  "texts": [
    "In addition to the main results at 1.5B reported in Section 4, we conducted additional experiments at 3B.",
    "The verifiable baseline, RLVR, exhibits a performance regression, dropping from 57.7% at 1.5B to 53.5% at 3B (Figure 9).",
    "Similarly, we observe that the performance of RARO also degrades from 54.4% to 49.7% at 3B.",
    "Furthermore, as illustrated in Figure 10, after inital improvements, both RLVR and RARO performance actively decreases as trainiing progresses.",
    "While we do not have a definitive explanation, we hypothesize that larger models may be more prone to the training-inference log-probability mismatch problem (Yao et al., 2025), leading to degradation when scaling model capacity."
  ],
